<span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 06, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kww1665703003587.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kww1665703003587.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kww1665703003587.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kww1665703003587\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"kww1665703003587__apstart_210186\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Pass control of the application to the component manager.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kww1665703003587__topic_d69677e1_d69678e1_d69679e1\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69680e1_d69681e1_d69682e1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"kww1665703003587__codeblock_ndk_ztz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">apstart</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kww1665703003587__topic_d45652e1_d45653e1_d45654e1_d45655e1_d45656e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d601663e65\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69686e1_d69687e1_d69688e1\">The values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> following <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> are:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kww1665703003587__li_d31748e1_d31749e1_d31750e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-1</code> if an error occurred. In this case, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> contains the exact error.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kww1665703003587__li_d31751e1_d31752e1_d31753e1\">Otherwise, the value returned by the last component or operation that ends. (It is not a good idea to return <code class=\"ph codeph\">-1</code> from components or operations, since this situation cannot be distinguished from the statement occurring in an incorrect trigger.)\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> that are commonly returned by\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1__entry__2\">\n Error Constant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1__entry__3\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1__entry__1\">\n 1402\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1__entry__2\">\n &lt;UPROCERR_STATEMENT&gt;\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kww1665703003587__table_d6101e1_d6102e1_d6103e1__entry__3\">\n Statement not allowed in this trigger. (The apstart statement is allowed only in the apStart trigger.)\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kww1665703003587__topic_d45657e1_d45658e1_d45659e1_d45660e1_d45661e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d601663e149\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69692e1_d69693e1_d69694e1\">Allowed only in the apStart trigger of application shells.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kww1665703003587__topic_d45662e1_d45663e1_d45664e1_d45665e1_d45666e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d601663e158\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69698e1_d69699e1_d69700e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> is required in the apStart trigger of the startup shells of a Uniface Server. It is usually not required in the startup shells of other applications. (In prior versions, it was needed in the apStart trigger after activating a sequence of non-modal forms before allowing the user to take control of the application session. Uniface automatically detects the activation of a sequence of non-modal forms and, after the last activate, passes control to the user. )</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69701e1_d69702e1_d69703e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> statement allows the component manager to take control of the application, waiting for user input. It can be used only in the apStart trigger.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69704e1_d69705e1_d69706e1\">The apStart trigger is typically used to start a number of non-modal forms before allowing the user to take control of the application session. If no forms are present in the component pool when <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> is encountered, the application terminates.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kww1665703003587__topic_d45667e1_d45668e1_d45669e1_d45670e1_d45671e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d601663e183\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> with Exception Handling\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kww1665703003587__p_d69710e1_d69711e1_d69712e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> statement is the call stack parent of all interactive triggers of a non-modal form, and many exceptions bubble through it when exception handling is enabled. To catch a specific exception thrown by an interactive trigger while a non-modal form is waiting for user input and Uniface is in idle mode, put a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try-catch</span> around the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apstart</span> statement in the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apStart</span> trigger of the parent application shell.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529414\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529414\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "apstart Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 06, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Pass control of the application to the component manager. apstart Copy Return Values The values returned in $status following apstart are: -1 if an error occurred. In this case, $procerror contains the exact error. Otherwise, the value returned by the last component or operation that ends. (It is not a good idea to return -1 from components or operations, since this situation cannot be distinguished from the statement occurring in an incorrect trigger.) Table 1. Values of $procerror that are commonly returned by apstart Value Error Constant Meaning 1402 <UPROCERR_STATEMENT> Statement not allowed in this trigger. (The apstart statement is allowed only in the apStart trigger.) Use Allowed only in the apStart trigger of application shells. Description The apstart is required in the apStart trigger of the startup shells of a Uniface Server. It is usually not required in the startup shells of other applications. (In prior versions, it was needed in the apStart trigger after activating a sequence of non-modal forms before allowing the user to take control of the application session. Uniface automatically detects the activation of a sequence of non-modal forms and, after the last activate, passes control to the user. ) The apstart statement allows the component manager to take control of the application, waiting for user input. It can be used only in the apStart trigger. The apStart trigger is typically used to start a number of non-modal forms before allowing the user to take control of the application session. If no forms are present in the component pool when apstart is encountered, the application terminates. apstart with Exception Handling The apstart statement is the call stack parent of all interactive triggers of a non-modal form, and many exceptions bubble through it when exception handling is enabled. To catch a specific exception thrown by an interactive trigger while a non-modal form is waiting for user input and Uniface is in idle mode, put a try-catch around the apstart statement in the apStart trigger of the parent application shell. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}